\f0\b\fs36 \ul Exporting a Proof (PNG):
\f1\b0 \

\fs24 \ulnone For proofing, it is preferred that the hat design is seen on the hat graphic. In order to accomplish this, you will have to export a PNG file as your proof. The following will explain how to export a PNG proof from within Illustrator:\
\
1. In Illustrator, go to File \uc0\u8594  Export \u8594  Export As. Select PNG from the format dropdown in the following window and hit OK.\
\
2. In the PNG Options window, make sure the resolution is set to High (300 ppi), the Anti-aliasing is set to Art Optimized (Supersampling), and the background color is set to Transparent. Then click Ok.\
\
3. The resulting PNG should have a transparent background with your graphic on the hat image in the position that you desire it to be on the physical hat itself.\
\
